{
  "stem": "21004.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Oh, my grandfather, he was very religious.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But the kids, the grandchildren, starting to get even a little more modern.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we were going to shul every Saturday.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We were [INAUDIBLE] put on tefillin, you know, and-- whenever you were home.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Later when we were out of home was a different story, so you also then Saturdays to shul.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But-- and-- we-- we were quite, but not over-done, not over-done religious.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh yes, right by the wedding she had a wig.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Had her hair before the wedding, he shared a wig to the wedding.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Religious education, we didn't go like actually to a regular like a cheder, a Jewish school, because my mother couldn't afford to send us.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And in the village, once we had somebody come and Hebrew teach and learn us, a rabbi to learn us, but very seldom.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But we had an uncle, my mother's father.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was a very intelligent, highly intelligent-- all languages.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He speaked a lot of languages, even Arabic.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he was-- he had a lot of-- a lot of thinking himself.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But it's really a genius.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He played violin, beautiful violin.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he played chess, the best chess player.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And-- and also a artist, artistically, you know, painting what he teached us.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And he teached us everything from [NON-ENGLISH] to Russia.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And not [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He don't believe so much a [NON-ENGLISH], just [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "His-- his favorite was [NON-ENGLISH], all the books.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He was really a genius.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "He was learning later.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "In Krakow, he was learning with people after shul.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "At night, they come, 300, 400 people.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And he was learning with them, you know, from the [NON-ENGLISH], from the-- from the Shabbas, Saturday's reading of the Torah, all kind of-- very intelligent person.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we learned a little bit, not too much.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
